Package: ChromDMM
Type: Package
Title: A Dirichlet-Multinomial Mixture Model For Clustering Heterogeneous Epigenetic Data
Version: 1.0
Author: Maria Osmala <maria.osmala@aalto.fi>, Goekcen Eraslan <geraslan@broadinstitute.org>, Martin Morgan <mtmorgan@fhcrc.org>
Maintainer: Maria Osmala <maria.osmala@aalto.fi>
Description: This package implements a Dirichlet-Multinomial mixture model to cluster multiple chromatin features simultaenously.
    The package is an extension of bioconductor packages DirichletMultinomial: Dirichlet-Multinomial Mixture Model 
    Machine Learning for Microbiome Data by Martin Morgan. DirichletMultinomial is  an interface to code originally 
    made available by Holmes,Harris, and Quince, 2012, PLoS ONE 7(2): 1-15, ?ChromDMM.
License: LGPL-3
Imports: Rcpp, stats4, methods, Matrix, ggplot2, grid, reshape2, GGally, plyr, mgcv, e1071, parallel, S4Vectors, IRanges
Suggests: lattice, MASS, RColorBrewer, xtable, testthat
Collate:
  AllGenerics.R
  util.R
  dmn.R
  dmn.em.R
  dmn.em.flip.R
  dmn.em.shift.R
  dmn.em.shift.flip.R
  dmngroup.R
  roc.R
  dmn_main.R
  dmn_graphics.R
  RcppExports.R
SystemRequirements: GNU GSL
NeedsCompilation: yes
biocViews: HighThroughputSequencing, Clustering, Classification
LinkingTo: Rcpp, RcppArmadillo, RcppGSL
